ProtoResult:
. "Let $a, b\in\mathbf{Q}$. Then for any integer $n$, $$\# 
   ((a,b)\cap \mathbf{Z} ) \equiv \# ((a,b+2n)\cap \mathbf{Z} )
   \pmod{2}$$ and $$ \# ((a,b)\cap \mathbf{Z} ) \equiv \# 
   ((a-2n,b)\cap \mathbf{Z} ) \pmod{2}, $$ provided that each 
   interval involved in the congruence is nonempty."
